# Short Code Comments

Every code comment block MUST be **fewer than 20 words**.

## Rules

- A single `//` line or a contiguous group of `//` lines counts as one block.
- If you need to say more, split into multiple short blocks separated by code (or just don't — brevity is the goal).
- Prefer naming things well over explaining them with a comment.
- Doc-comments on exported types/functions follow the same rule per sentence.
- If you believe a longer comment is genuinely necessary, **ask the user** before writing it.

## Examples

<bad>

```go
// The just-fired durable timer has already been consumed by the task processor
// and removed from the queue, so the run's reference to it is now dangling.
// Clear it unconditionally regardless of what we do next — whether we dispatch
// (a step is Satisfied) or stay in AllStepsWaiting with no timer condition left
// to re-arm (e.g. only channel waits remain).
update.ActiveDurableTimerID = ptr.Any("")
```

</bad>

<good>

```go
// Clear dangling timer ref — task processor already consumed it.
update.ActiveDurableTimerID = ptr.Any("")
```

</good>

## Review checklist

- Reject any comment block that is 20 words or more. Rewrite it shorter.
- If you cannot shorten below 20 words without losing critical info, ask the user to confirm before committing it.
